Almost a dive bar with the amount of locals here, but throw in a nearby college and you get a decent amount of the younger crowd. Service isn't great, but if I had to deal with drunk college kids all night I wouldn't be the nicest bartender either. Pool tables available; a dance floor for weekends; and a nice patio in the back; prices in line for a typical bar. Parking is limited in downtown Westfield, and the best spot is in the bank parking lot behind the bar. On a positive note, the security/bouncers are pretty cool people who are laid back but keep things clean.
